{"title_page": "Mersal (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2017 Indian film directed by Atlee}}\n{{use Indian English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Mersal\n| image          = Mersal Theatrical Release Poster.jpg<!-- This is a recently updated poster of this film, which is also in english. Hence, please do not change this film poster further.-->\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Atlee (director)|Atlee Kumar]]\n| producer       = N. Ramasamy<br />Hema Rukmani<br />H. Murali\n| screenplay     = [[Atlee (director)|Atlee Kumar]]<br />[[K. V. Vijayendra Prasad]]<br />S. Ramana Girivasan\n| story          = [[Atlee (director)|Atlee Kumar]]\n| starring       = [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]]<br>[[Kajal Aggarwal]]<br>[[Samantha (actress)|Samantha]]<br>[[Nithya Menen]]<br>[[S. J. Surya]]<br>[[Vadivelu]]<br>[[Sathyaraj]]\n| music          = '''Songs:'''<br>[[A. R. Rahman]]<br>'''Score:'''<br>A. R. Rahman<br>[[Qutub-E-Kripa]]\n| cinematography = [[G. K. Vishnu]]\n| editing        = [[Ruben (editor)|Ruben]]\n| studio         = [[Sri Thenandal Films|Thenandal Studio Limited]]\n| distributor    = {{ubl|[[Sri Thenandal Films]] (Tamil Nadu) |North Star Entertainment (Andhra Pradesh and Telangana) |[[S. Narayan]] (Karnataka) |[[Global United Media]] (Kerala)}}\n| released       = {{film date|2017|10|18|Worldwide|df=y|ref1=<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/vijays-mersal-release-date-is-here.html|title=Vijay's Mersal release date is here|date=8 October 2017|publisher=|accessdate=2 November 2017}}</ref>}}\n| runtime        = 169 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = {{INR}}120 [[crore]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/mersal-box-office-collection-thalapathy-vijay-atlee/1/1083305.html|title=Mersal box office collection: Vijays film crosses Rs 20 crore in Kerala|publisher=|accessdate=17 November 2017}}</ref>\n| gross          = {{Estimation}}{{INR}}260 crore<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.in.com/entertainment/regional/bigils-budget-crosses-the-140-crore-mark-making-it-the-most-expensive-vijay-film-till-date-472381.htm|title=Bigil's budget crosses the 140-crore-mark; making it the most expensive Vijay film till date!|website=in.com|language=en|access-date=8 August 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"260c\">{{Cite web|url=https://tamil.samayam.com/tamil-cinema/movie-news/sarkar-beats-mersal-lifetime-collections-breaches-260-crore-mark/articleshow/66783172.cms|title=\u0b85\u0b9f\u0bc7\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe, \u0baa\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0b86\u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0b9a\u0bc2\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b87\u0bb5\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bb3\u0bb5\u0bbe? \u0bae\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0ba9\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0baf\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 '\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd'!|date=24 November 2018|website=[[The Times Group|Samayam Tamil]]|language=ta|access-date=12 February 2019}}</ref>([[#Box office|see{{nbsp}}below]])\n}}\n\n'''''Mersal''''' ({{Translation|zapped}}) is a 2017 Indian [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[action thriller film]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/mersal-film|title=MERSAL&nbsp;\u2014 British Board of Film Classification|website=www.bbfc.co.uk|accessdate=2 November 2017}}</ref> directed by [[Atlee (director)|Atlee]] and co-written by Atlee, [[K. V. Vijayendra Prasad]] and S. Ramana Girivasan, in charge of the dialogues, and produced by [[Thenandal Studio Limited]], thus becoming their 100th production. The film stars [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] in a triple role as a father and his twin sons alongside [[Kajal Aggarwal]], [[Samantha (actress)|Samantha]], and [[Nithya Menen]] as the female leads, while [[S. J. Surya|S.J.Suryah]], [[Vadivelu]] and [[Sathyaraj]] amongst other portray supporting roles.\n\nThe story revolves around two twin brothers in which one is a [[magician (illusionist)|magician]] avenging for his father's death and medical crimes. The other one is a reputed doctor who charges meagre amounts from his patients. The film's principal photography commenced on 1 February 2017, at Chennai, and filming took place on [[Gda\u0144sk]], [[Poland]] and [[Jaisalmer]], [[Rajasthan]]. The background score and soundtrack album were composed by [[A. R. Rahman]], while the cinematography was done by [[G. K. Vishnu]] and edited by [[Ruben (editor)|Ruben]].\n\n''Mersal'' was released worldwide on 18 October 2017, coinciding with [[Diwali]] and opened to positive reviews with critics praising the performance of Vijay, A. R. Rahman's soundtrack, the cinematography, the social message and [[Atlee Kumar|Atlee's]] direction, but criticised the [[clich\u00e9]] plot and excessive length. The film was a commercial success, grossing \u20b9260 crore ({{US$|{{To USD|2600|IND|round=yes}} million}}) worldwide, becoming the fifth-highest grossing Indian Tamil film and Vijay's highest-grossing film in his career. The film's dubbed Telugu version ''Adirnidhi'' released on 9 November 2017. The film completed 100-day theatrical run on 25 January 2018.<ref name=\"260c\" /><ref name=\"total\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/mersal-box-office-collection-vijay-samanthas-film-completes-100-days-758196|title=Mersal box office collection: Vijay, Samantha's film completes 100 days|last=Upadhyaya|first=Prakash|work=International Business Times, India Edition|access-date=26 January 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businesstoday.in/buzztop/buzztop-feature/sarkar-box-office-collection-vijay-starrer-collects-rs-214-crore-in-first-10-days/story/291630.html|title=Sarkar box office collection: Vijay-starrer collects Rs 214 crore in first 10 days|website=www.businesstoday.in|language=en|access-date=8 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe film was released on 6 December 2018 in [[China]] by HGC Entertainment.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/thalapathy-vijays-mersal-to-release-in-china.html|title=Thalapathy Vijay's Mersal to release in China|date=10 August 2018|work=Behindwoods|access-date=10 August 2018}}</ref> Due to demand, the film was screened at the largest cinema theatre in Europe [[Grand Rex]], France.<ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/mersal-fever-in-france.html|title=Mersal fever in France|date=13 October 2017|website=Behindwoods|access-date=7 February 2019}}</ref> The film was screened at the [[Hainan International Film Festival]] in [[Hainan]], China<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=http://chinafilminsider.com/headlines-from-china-live-streaming-platform-panda-tv-rumored-to-file-for-bankruptcy/|title=Headlines from China: Live Streaming Platform Panda TV Rumored to File for Bankruptcy|date=7 March 2019|website=China Film Insider|access-date=14 March 2019}}</ref> and at the [[Bucheon International Fantastic Film Festival]] in [[South Korea]].<ref name=\":9\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/vijays-mersal-screened-at-bifan-film-festival.html|title=Vijay's Mersal screened at BIFAN Film Festival|date=30 July 2018|website=Behindwoods|access-date=14 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\n<!--per [[WP:FILMPLOT]], plot summaries should be between 400 and 700 words-->\nAn ambulance driver, a broker, a hospital [[human resources|HR]] and a surgeon are abducted under mysterious circumstances at dawn. The abductions are traced to Dr. Maaran, a world-famous doctor from [[Chennai]] known for providing {{INR}}5 treatment to patients of all sections of society. Maaran is arrested and interrogated by Ratnavel \"Randy\", a police officer who is assigned the abduction case. Maaran explains his motive for the abductions; An Auto Driver's daughter had been severely injured and  the four were responsible for the death of the auto driver's school-going daughter and his wife due to their greed for money in the name of providing proper healthcare. He adds that he had also killed all of them while they were in his captivity.\n\nAt this juncture, Maaran reveals that he is not Maaran but is his [[doppelg\u00e4nger]] Vetri, a [[Magician (illusionist)|magician]].Vetri was responsible for the death of Dr. Arjun Zachariah, a corrupt doctor who was killed during a stage performance in Paris two years earlier,by Vetri himself by using  Anupallavi who is also his love interest. He further adds that he had saved Maaran from getting killed by the henchmen of Dr. Daniel Arockiyaraj.Daniel,another corrupt doctor had been associated with Arjun who sees Maaran's inexpensive healthcare as a threat to his flourishing hospital business.After beating them up,Vetri knocks out Maaran unconscious and swaps place with him.Then he provides clues to the police which led to his arrest as showed in the beginning. Maaran is rescued, while Vetri, with the help of his magic tricks, manages to escape from Randy.\n\nLater, Maaran confronts Vetri and fights him, believing him to be the cause of all his problems with the law as well as with Daniel, who had threatened Maaran to reveal the location of Vetri while keeping his mother Sarala and fianc\u00e9e Tara hostage. Vadivu, Maaran's compounder and also Vetri's assistant, intervenes in their fight and explains to Maaran why Vetri is targeting doctors indulging in corrupt medical practices in general and Daniel and Arjun in particular.\n\nMaaran was the elder son of Vetrimaaran, a village [[wrestling|wrestler]].Vetrimaaran being referred as Thalapathy by his villagers,decides to build a temple in his area.He holds a large scale event for the building day with a festive mode.However,a fire had started causing many people and children to get injured and two children had died due to their lack of mobility.By the advice of Ice,Vetrimaaran had established a hospital with the help of a younger Daniel and Arjun in his village Manoor in [[Madurai district]]. Daniel and Arjun were also made as the chief doctors of the hospital.\n\nHowever, it soon turns out that Daniel and Arjun were money-minded crooks and performed a [[Caesarean section]] on Vetrimaaran's wife Aishwarya \"Ice\" when she was in labour with her second child, with the intention of extracting more money from Vetrimaaran, even though she could deliver the child [[vaginal delivery|normally]]. Ice lost a lot of blood during the operation, and that, along with an overdose of [[anaesthesia]], led to her death, while the child was declared [[stillborn]]. When Vetrimaaran found out how Ice had died, he went to confront Daniel, empty beer bottles start to hit him and the back of Vetrimaaran was stabbed to death by one of Daniel's henchmen, but just before he died, he placed an unconscious Maaran (who had been struck on the head with a glass bottle by Daniel's henchman) safely on a Chennai-bound lorry. Due to the impact the glass bottle had on his head, Maaran lost his memory and is unable to recollect anything that happened before he was hit on the head.\n\nMeanwhile, Vetrimaaran's second child did not turn out to be stillborn, and this child was none other than Vetri. Vetri was adopted by a famous magician named Salim Ghosh, and it was from him that Vetri learnt all his magic tricks. On hearing Vadivu's story, Maaran reconciles with Vetri and takes his place when police come to arrest Vetri. With Vetri (who is actually Maaran) seemingly in custody, Daniel tries to make a deal with Maaran (who is actually Vetri) to shut down his practice. However, when he finds out the truth, he rushes to Vetri's hideout, bringing with him an unconscious Maaran, who had met with an accident orchestrated by Daniel while he was being taken to court, with the intention of killing both Vetri and Maaran. However, Vetri and Maaran, with the help of their respective professional skills, team up to kill Daniel.\n\nLater, however, Vetri is arrested for his role in the murders of Daniel and Arjun as well as the four people killed earlier in the film and is sentenced to prison for an unspecified period of time. Before going to jail, he gives a press conference justifying his actions and adds that he would continue with the murders until all doctors and hospital staff indulging in corrupt practices are eliminated. In prison, Vetri watches a news report in which a young girl in [[Odisha]] had died due to negligent medical treatment. On hearing this, Vetri escapes with the help of his magic tricks, thus continuing his mission. In a mid-credits scene, Maaran is conferred a statewide recognised medical counsellor post, which he accepts.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] in a triple role as\n**Vetrimaaran, a village wrestler, commonly referred by the people as \"Thalapathy\" and who gets killed by Daniel and Kasi\n**Dr. Maaran, Vetrimaaran's first son, a doctor who serves people for just 5 rupees and gets conferred a statewide medical counsellor post\n**Vetri, Vetrimaaran's second son, a magician and Maaran's younger brother who gets arrested for his role in the murders\n* [[Kajal Aggarwal]] as Anu Pallavi, Vetri's love interest, a doctor and Arjun's assistant\n* [[Samantha Ruth Prabhu]] as Thara, a media anchor and Maaran's love interest\n* [[Nithya Menen]] as Aishwarya \"Ice\" Vetrimaaran, Vetrimaaran's wife who dies in a hospital due to blood loss and overdose of anaesthesia \n* [[S. J. Surya]] as Daniel Arockiyaraj, a greedy and corrupt doctor who kills Vetrimaaran\n* [[Vadivelu]] as Vadivu, Maaran's compounder and Vetri's assistant\n* [[Sathyaraj]] as DC Rathnavel \"Randy\", a police officer with Tamil Nadu Police\n* [[Kovai Sarala]] as Sarala, Maaran's adoptive mother who gets taken hostage by Daniel\n* [[Hareesh Peradi]] as Arjun Zachariah, Daniel's friend and another doctor who gets killed while performing a magic trick\n* [[Rajendran]] as Minister of Health\n* [[Sathyan (Tamil actor)|Sathyan]] as Maniya, Rathnavel's assistant\n<!-- as Jikli, Anu Pallavi's friend-->\n* [[Yogi Babu]] as Nolan\n* [[Misha Ghoshal]] as Tara's friend\n* [[Mamilla Shailaja Priya]] as Tara's mother\n* [[Sangili Murugan]] as Salim Ghosh, a magician who taught magic to Vetri\n* [[Kaali Venkat]] as the auto driver whose daughter meets with an accident and whose wife commits suicide\n* [[Devadarshini]] as Nurse\n* [[Surekha Vani]] as Nurse\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\n=== Development ===\nFollowing the release of Atlee's ''[[Theri (film)|Theri]]'', in which Vijay starred, the pair was signed by [[Sri Thenandal Films]] for another project together in September 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/sri-thenandal-films-signs-ilayathalapathy-vijay-news-tamil-qjjkwnjbfbjbd.html|title=Sri Thenandal Films signs Ilayathalapathy Vijay?|publisher=|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/vijay-60-bairavaa-star-collaborate-atlee-sri-thenandal-films-693082|title='Vijay 60': 'Bairavaa' star to collaborate with Atlee, Sri Thenandal Films|first=Prakash|last=Upadhyaya|publisher=|accessdate=24 May 2017|date=9 September 2016}}</ref> Safwan Saleem, the chief executive officer of the production house, revealed that the film would be written by writer [[K. V. Vijayendra Prasad]], who had earlier worked in films like the ''[[Baahubali: The Beginning|Baahubali]]'' series and ''[[Bajrangi Bhaijaan]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/vijay-61-sri-thenandal-films-confirms-producing-ilayathalapathy-atlees-film-700191|title=Vijay 61: Sri Thenandal Films confirms producing Ilayathalapathy, Atlee's film|first=Prakash|last=Upadhyaya|publisher=|accessdate=24 May 2017|date=19 October 2016}}</ref> The action sequences of the film are directed by [[Anal Arasu]]. Atlee's usual cinematographer [[George C. Williams (cinematographer)|George C. Williams]] whom worked for ''[[Raja Rani (2013 film)|Raja Rani]]'' and ''[[Theri (film)|Theri]]'', was supposed to work in this film too, but failed due to clash with his other project. [[G. K. Vishnu]] was signed later on making his debut in this film.<ref>Kumar, Karthik (20 March 2017) [http://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/no-thalapathi-title-for-ilayathalapathy-vijay-s-film-with-sri-thenandal-films/story-VcpMdg4GWc4cQOr9YnPbNK.html No thalapathi title for Ilayathalapathy Vijay's film with Sri Thenandal Films!]. ''Hindustan Times''. Retrieved on 4 October 2017.</ref> Vijay learnt a few magic tricks in preparation for his role as the magician. He learnt the magic tricks from three magicians: Gogo Requiem from the [[Republic of Macedonia]], Raman Sharma from Canada, and Dani Belev from [[Bulgaria]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/060817/vijay-learns-a-few-tricks-for-mersal.html|title=Vijay learns a few tricks for Mersal|date=6 August 2017|work=www.deccanchronicle.com/|access-date=7 August 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\n=== Casting ===\n[[File:Ayuntamiento Principal, Gdansk, Polonia, 2013-05-20, DD 02.jpg|thumb|right|The city of [[Gda\u0144sk]], [[Poland]], served as Paris for the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/vijays-mersal-will-not-be-releasing-in-inox-and-pvr-theatres-chennai.html|title=Vijay's Mersal will not be releasing in Inox and PVR theatres chennai|date=17 October 2017|publisher=|accessdate=17 November 2017}}</ref>]]\nThe producers announced in January 2017 that three lead actresses{{Spaced ndash|}}[[Jyothika]], [[Kajal Aggarwal]] and [[Samantha (actress)|Samantha]] would portray the female lead-roles in the film. The production team later revealed that due to some unavoidable reasons actress Jyothika opted out of the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/jyothika-walks-out-of-atlee-kumar-vijay-61-nithya-menen-replaces-her-real-reason-why/|title=Revealed! The real reason why Jyothika opted out of Vijay 61 - Bollywoodlife.com|publisher=|date=7 February 2017}}</ref>  The role went to [[Nithya Menon]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/nithya-menen-signs-vijay-61-why-did-jyothika-walk-out-ilayathalapathys-film-715093|title=Nithya Menen signs Vijay 61; why did Jyothika walk out of Ilayathalapathy's film?|first=Prakash|last=Upadhyaya|publisher=|date=7 February 2017}}</ref> Actors [[S. J. Suryah]] and [[Sathyaraj]] also joined the cast as supporting actors, with comedians [[Vadivelu]], [[Kovai Sarala]], [[Sathyan (Tamil actor)|Sathyan]] and [[Rajendran]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/vijay-61-ilayathalapathy-vijay-jyothika-kajal-samantha/1/871842.html |title= Ilayathalapathy Vijay to romance Kajal, Samantha, nithya menon in his next|publisher=|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref> Suryah is playing villainous role with two looks in the movie.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.top10cinema.com/article/42292/vijay-61-official-news-on-first-look-and-theatrical-release|title=Vijay 61 official news on firstk look and theatrical release|date=22 April 2017|work=Top 10 Cinema|access-date=22 April 2017|language=en-US}}</ref> Composer [[A. R. Rahman]], editor [[Ruben (editor)|Ruben]], costume designer [[Neeraja Kona]] and debutant cinematographer G. K. Vishnu, an erstwhile assistant of [[Richard M. Nathan]] were also a part to the technical team.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/sri-thenandal-films-officially-announce-the-cast-and-crew-details-about-vijay-61.html|title=Sri Thenandal Films officially announces the cast and crew details about Vijay 61|date=31 January 2017|publisher=|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref><ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Vijay-Vadivelu-team-up-for-a-cop-act/articleshow/46476018.cms Vjiay: Vijay, Vadivelu team up for a cop act]. ''Times of India'' (16 January 2017). Retrieved on 4 October 2017.</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\nA launch event for the film was held at Adityaram Studios in [[Chennai]] on 1 February 2017, with production beginning thereafter.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/vijay-61-aka-thalapathy-61-movie-launch-ilayathalapathy-atlee-film-hit-floors-714283|title=Vijay 61 aka Thalapathy 61 movie launched: The shooting of Ilayathalapathy-Atlee film begins|first=Prakash|last=Upadhyaya|publisher=|accessdate=24 May 2017|date=31 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/nithya-menen-replaces-jyothika-in-thalapathy-61-news-tamilk-rcgsptdacgcaj.html|title=Nithya Menen replaces Jyothika in 'Thalapathy 61'|publisher=|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref> The team has decided to shoot a with [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] and [[Kajal Aggarwal]] song in [[Jaisalmer]] during the summer despite the hot weather.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.top10cinema.com/article/42069/vijay-nithya-menen-in-hot-backdrops-of-jai-salmer|title=Vijay-Nithya Menen in hot backdrops of Jai Salmer|date=5 April 2017|work=Top 10 Cinema|access-date=5 April 2017|language=en-US}}</ref> The steam engine named 7161WP AKBAR was used in this movie while shooting in [[Rajasthan]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.top10cinema.com/article/42218/vijay-61-brings-back-rajasthani-heritage|title=Vijay 61 brings back Rajasthani heritage|date=17 April 2017|work=Top 10 Cinema|access-date=18 April 2017|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.keralanews247.com/vijay-61-new-clean-shaven-look-goes-viral-online/|title=Vijay 61 New clean-shaven look goes viral on Online {{!}} Latest News|date=18 April 2017|work=Latest News|access-date=18 April 2017|language=en-US}}</ref> Some of the filming was conducted in [[Poland]] ([[Gda\u0144sk]], [[Pozna\u0144]]<ref>{{in lang|pl}} [http://kultura.gazeta.pl/kultura/7,114438,22433495,zwiastun-hinduskiego-filmu-a-tam-stadion-w-gdansku-starowka.html#Czolka3Img Zwiastun hinduskiego filmu, a tam... Stadion w Gda\u0144sku, Pozna\u0144 i lotnisko im. Wa\u0142\u0119sy]. Kultura.gazeta.pl (27 September 2017). Retrieved on 4 October 2017.</ref> and [[Rzesz\u00f3w]]'s [[Rzesz\u00f3w\u2013Jasionka Airport|airport]]<ref>[http://rzeszow.eska.pl/poznaj-miasto/obiekt-g2a-arena-planem-indyjskiego-filmu-zobacz-zwiastun-wideo/570859 Obiekt G2A Arena planem indyjskiego filmu: Zobacz zwiastun [WIDEO&#93;&nbsp;\u2013 rzeszow.eskainfo.pl]. Rzeszow.eska.pl. Retrieved on 4 October 2017.</ref>), as well as in [[Skopje]], Republic of Macedonia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thenews.pl/1/11/Artykul/308356,Bollywood-movie-to-be-shot-in-Poland|title=Bollywood movie to be shot in Poland|publisher=|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref> The shooting was held in Chennai, Jaisalmer, Rajasthan and [[Konaseema]] in Andhra Pradesh, while the songs were filmed overseas. It is reported that, due to indefinite strike announced by [[Film Employees Federation of South India]], ''Mersal'' team were waiting to film few portions of the movie, which has now been completed.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.top10cinema.com/article/43941/inevitable-fefsi-strike-delayed-release-of-mersal-velaikkaran-and-karuppan|title=Inevitable FEFSI Strike&nbsp;\u2013 Delayed release of Mersal, Velaikkaran and Karuppan?|date=7 September 2017|work=Top 10 Cinema|access-date=8 September 2017|language=en-US}}</ref>\n{{clear}}\n\n== Themes and influences ==\nThe character Maaran (or {{Indian Rupee|5}} doctor), played by Vijay in the film, was inspired from Dr. Balasubramanian, a doctor who hails from [[Bodinayakkanur]], [[Theni]] district, and charges {{Indian Rupee|2}} from patients. It is also known that Vijay's character Jeevanantham in ''[[Kaththi]]'' (2014), is inspired from a real-life social activist.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/is-mersals-5-rupees-doctor-inspired-by-late-drbalasubramanian-from-theni.html|title=Is Mersal's 5 rupees doctor inspired by late Dr.Balasubramanian from Theni|date=19 October 2017|website=Behindwoods|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nCritics noted that the film has similarities related to [[Rajinikanth]]-starrer ''[[Moondru Mugam]]'' (1982),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/mersal-director-atlee-accused-plagiarism-89691?amp|website=www.thenewsminute.com|access-date=27 March 2020|title='Mersal' director Atlee accused of plagiarism|date=9 October 2018}}</ref> and [[Kamal Haasan]]'s [[Apoorva Sagodharargal (1989 film)|''Apoorva Sagodharargal'']] (1989; ''Appu Raja'' in [[Hindi]]).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/mersal-may-be-a-triumph-for-its-star-vijay-but-what-does-it-say-about-its-director-atlee-4158441.html|title=Mersal may be a triumph for its star Vijay, but what does it say about its director Atlee? - Entertainment News, Firstpost|last=21 Oct|first=Firstpost \u2022|last2=Ist|first2=2017 14:14|website=Firstpost|date=20 October 2017|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Music ==\n[[A. R. Rahman]] composed the soundtrack album and background score of ''Mersal'', teaming up with [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] for the third time, after his films ''[[Udhaya]]'' (2004), and ''[[Azhagiya Tamil Magan|Azhagiya Tamizh Magan]]'' (2007), and his first collaboration with [[Atlee Kumar|Atlee]]. The lyrics for the film were written by [[Vivek (lyricist)|Vivek]], who also teams up with Rahman for the first time. The audio rights of the film were acquired by [[Sony Music India]], for a record price.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2017/jul/25/record-price-for-vijay-starrer-mersal-audio-rights-1633014.amp|title=Record price for Mersal audio rights - The New Indian Express|website=www.newindianexpress.com|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n\"[[Aalaporaan Thamizhan]]\", a song from the film was released as a single on 10 August 2017, sung by [[Kailash Kher]],<ref name=\":2\">[http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/shreya-ghoshal-and-kailash-kher-recorded-a-melody-song-for-vijays-mersal.html Shreya Ghoshal and Kailash Kher recorded a melody song for Vijay's Mersal]. Behindwoods.com (29 July 2017). Retrieved on 4 October 2017.</ref> Sathya Prakash, Deepak and [[Pooja Vaidyanath]], portrays about the popularity of Tamil speaking men all over the world. The second single track \"Neethanae\" sung by [[Shreya Ghoshal]] and Rahman was released on 17 August 2017.<ref name=\":2\" /> The album features other remaining songs \"Maacho\" sung by [[Sid Sriram]] and [[Shweta Mohan]], and \"Mersal Arasan\" sung by [[G. V. Prakash Kumar]], [[Naresh Iyer]], [[Sharanya Srinivas]], T. G. Vishwaprasad.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite news|url=https://silverscreen.in/tamil/news/gv-prakash-kumar-to-sing-for-vijays-mersal/|title=GV Prakash Kumar To Sing For Vijay's 'Mersal'&nbsp;\u2013 Silverscreen.in|date=18 August 2017|work=Silverscreen.in|access-date=19 August 2017|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nThe audio launch event was held on 20 August 2017, at [[Jawaharlal Nehru Indoor Stadium]] in [[Chennai]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/wait-over-vijays-mersal-audio-release-date-out-65675?amp|title=The wait is over! Vijay's Mersal audio release date is out!|last=|first=|date=24 July 2017|website=www.thenewsminute.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/music/mersal-audio-launch-on-august-20/articleshow/59710594.cms|title=Mersal audio launch on August 20 - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref> The event was telecasted live on the official [[YouTube]] channel of [[Sony Music India|Sony Music South]], [[Facebook]] and [[Twitter]] accounts of the production house. It was rumoured that the live telecast of the launch will be aired in three television channels,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://onlookersmedia.in/latestnews/massive-mersal-audio-launch-telecasted-live-3-tv-channels/|title=Massive! Mersal audio launch to be telecasted live on 3 TV channels|last=Madhu|first=Vignesh|date=16 August 2017|website=onlookersmedia|language=en-US|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref> however it was aired live on [[Sun TV (India)|Sun TV]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.behindwoods.com/amp/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/sun-tv-has-taken-over-mersal-audio-launch-coverage.html0|title=Sun TV has taken over Mersal audio launch coverage!|last=|first=|date=18 August 2017|website=Behindwoods|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref> The film's cast and crew and other celebrities such as [[Dhanush]], [[Sundar C.|Sundar. C]], amongst others were attended at the event, which was hosted by [[R. Parthiban]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/mersal-music-live-update-vijay-arrives-early-at-the-venue-to-welcome-the-guests-and-his-fans-go-wild-1046983/|title=Mersal audio launch: Vijay, A R Rahman, Samantha Ruth Prabhu and Dhanush turn it into a gala night|date=20 August 2017|website=Bollywood Life|language=en|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref> Rahman and his musical team gave a stage performance at the audio launch.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/mersal-audio-launch-on-august-20-ar-rahman-may-perform-at-the-function/story-6oZWXrxyhUUwr0iKJhk65O.html|title=Mersal audio launch on August 20, AR Rahman may perform at the function|website=hindustantimes.com|date=4 August 2017|language=en|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/mersal-audio-release-vijay-steals-show-his-powerful-speech-photosvideo-739147|title=Mersal audio release: Vijay steals the show with his powerful speech [Photos+Video]|last=Upadhyaya|first=Prakash|date=21 August 2017|website=International Business Times, India Edition|language=en|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref>{{Infobox album\n| name         = Mersal\n| type         = [[Soundtrack]]\n| artist       = [[A. R. Rahman]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| caption      = Mersal Album Artwork\n| released     = 20 August 2017\n| recorded     = 